    "question": "Given the balanced chemical reaction: \n\n2 C6H8O7 (citric acid) + 3 Na2CO3 (sodium carbonate) -> 6 NaC6H5O7 (sodium citrate) + 3 CO2 (carbon dioxide) + 3 H2O (water)\n\nWhat are the combined weights of 3 moles of citric acid, 4.5 moles of sodium carbonate, 9 moles of sodium citrate, 4.5 moles of carbon dioxide, and 4.5 moles of water involved in this reaction?\n\n### Answer:",
    "options": [
      "Option A",
      "Option B",
      "Option C",
      "Option D"
    ],
    "correct": 0,
    "explanation": "To find the combined weights of the substances involved in the reaction, we need to calculate the molar mass of each substance and then multiply it by the number of moles given.\n\n1. Molar mass of C6H8O7 (citric acid):\nC: 12.01 g/mol * 6 = 72.06 g/mol\nH: 1.008 g/mol * 8 = 8.064 g/mol\nO: 16.00 g/mol * 7 = 112.00 g/mol\nTotal molar mass of C6H8O7 = 72.06 + 8.064 + 112.00 = 192.124 g/mol\n\nFor 3 moles of citric acid:\n3 moles * 192.124 g/mol = 576.372 g\n\n2. Molar mass of Na2CO3 (sodium carbonate):\nNa: 22.99 g/mol * 2 = 45.98 g/mol\nC: 12.01 g/mol = 12.01 g/mol\nO: 16.00 g/mol * 3 = 48.00 g/mol\nTotal molar mass of Na2CO3 = 45.98 + 12.01 + 48.00 = 105.99 g/mol\n\nFor 4.5 moles of sodium carbonate:\n4.5 moles * 105.99 g/mol = 477.455 g\n\n3. Molar mass of NaC6H5O7 (sodium citrate):\nNa: 22.99 g/mol * 3 = 68.97 g/mol\nC: 12.01 g/mol * 6 = 72.06 g/mol\nH: 1.008 g/mol * 5 = 5.04 g/mol\nO: 16.00 g/mol * 7 = 112.00 g/mol\nTotal molar mass of NaC6H5O7 = 68.97 + 72.06 + 5.04 + 112.00 = 258.07 g/mol\n\nFor 9 moles of sodium citrate:\n9 moles * 258.07 g/mol = 2322.63 g\n\n4. Molar mass of CO2 (carbon dioxide):\nC: 12.01 g/mol = 12.01 g/mol\nO: 16.00 g/mol * 2 = 32.00 g/mol\nTotal molar mass of CO2 = 12.01 + 32.00 = 44.01 g/mol\n\nFor 4.5 moles of carbon dioxide:\n4.5 moles * 44.01 g/mol = 198.045 g\n\n5. Molar mass of H2O (water):\nH: 1.008 g/mol * 2 = 2.016 g/mol\nO: 16.00 g/mol = 16.00 g/mol\nTotal molar mass of H2O = 2.016 + 16.00 = 18.016 g/mol\n\nFor 4.5 moles of water:\n4.5 moles * 18.016 g/mol = 81.072 g\n\nNow, we add the weights of all the substances:\n576.372 g (citric acid) + 477.455 g (sodium carbonate) + 2322.63 g (sodium citrate) + 198.045 g (carbon dioxide) + 81.072 g (water) = 3655.574 g\n\nThe combined weight of the substances involved in the reaction is 3655.574 grams.",
