    "explanation": "Let's calculate the total cost for each car model without the discount first, and then apply the discount where applicable.\n\nFor Model A cars:\n- Oil change: $20\n- Repair: $30\n- Car wash: $5\n- Total for one Model A car: $20 + $30 + $5 = $55\n- Since each Model A car had three services, they qualify for the 10% discount.\n- Discount for one Model A car: 10% of $55 = $5.50\n- Total for one Model A car after discount: $55 - $5.50 = $49.50\n- Total for 5 Model A cars: 5 * $49.50 = $247.50\n\nFor Model B cars:\n- Oil change: $25\n- Repair: $40\n- Car wash: $8\n- Tire rotation: $18\n- Total for one Model B car: $25 + $40 + $8 + $18 = $91\n- Since each Model B car had four services, they qualify for the 10% discount.\n- Discount for one Model B car: 10% of $91 = $9.10\n- Total for one Model B car after discount: $91 - $9.10 = $81.90\n- Total for 3 Model B cars: 3 * $81.90 = $245.70\n\nFor Model C cars:\n- Oil change: $30\n- Repair: $50\n- Tire rotation: $20\n- Car wash: $10\n- Total for one Model C car: $30 + $50 + $20 + $10 = $110\n- Since each Model C car had four services, they qualify for the 10% discount.\n- Discount for one Model C car: 10% of $110 = $11\n- Total for one Model C car after discount: $110 - $11 = $99\n- Total for 2 Model C cars: 2 * $99 = $198\n\nFor Model D cars:\n- Oil change: $35\n- Repair: $60\n- Tire rotation: $22\n- Total for one Model D car: $35 + $60 + $22 = $117\n- Since each Model D car had three services, they qualify for the 10% discount.\n- Discount for one Model D car: 10% of $117 = $11.70\n- Total for one Model D car after discount: $117 - $11.70 = $105.30\n- Total for 4 Model D cars: 4 * $105.30 = $421.20\n\nNow, let's add up the totals for all the cars:\nTotal earnings = Total for Model A + Total for Model B + Total for Model C + Total for Model D\nTotal earnings = $247.50 + $245.70 + $198 + $421.20\nTotal earnings = $1112.40\n\nCid earned $1112.40 that day after applying the discounts for multiple services.",
