    "correct": 0,
    "explanation": "To find Berry's average temperature for the week in each scale, we need to calculate the mean of his daily temperatures. We'll do this by adding up all the temperatures for each day of the week and then dividing by the total number of temperature readings.\n\n**In Celsius:**\n\\( (37.3 + 37.2 + 36.9 + 36.6 + 36.9 + 37.1 + 37.1 + 37.3 + 37.2 + 36.8 + 37.3 + 37.5 + 37.1 + 37.7 + 37.3 + 37.5 + 37.4 + 36.9 + 36.9 + 37.0 + 37.1) / 21 \\)\n\n**In Kelvin:**\n\\( (310.4 + 310.3 + 310.0 + 309.8 + 310.0 + 310.2 + 310.2 + 310.4 + 310.3 + 309.9 + 310.4 + 310.6 + 310.2 + 310.8 + 310.4 + 310.6 + 310.5 + 310.0 + 310.0 + 310.1 + 310.2) / 21 \\)\n\n**In Rankine:**\n\\( (558.7 + 558.6 + 558.1 + 557.7 + 558.1 + 558.3 + 558.3 + 558.7 + 558.6 + 558.0 + 558.7 + 559.1 + 558.3 + 559.4 + 558.7 + 559.1 + 558.9 + 558.1 + 558.1 + 558.2 + 558.3) / 21 \\)\n\nNow, let's calculate the sums and then the averages:\n\n**Celsius:**\n\\( 37.3 + 37.2 + 36.9 + 36.6 + 36.9 + 37.1 + 37.1 + 37.3 + 37.2 + 36.8 + 37.3 + 37.5 + 37.1 + 37.7 + 37.3 + 37.5 + 37.4 + 36.9 + 36.9 + 37.0 + 37.1 = 779.4 \\)\nAverage in Celsius: \\( 779.4 / 21 = 37.1143 \\) (rounded to four decimal places)\n\n**Kelvin:**\n\\( 310.4 + 310.3 + 310.0 + 309.8 + 310.0 + 310.2 + 310.2 + 310.4 + 310.3 + 309.9 + 310.4 + 310.6 + 310.2 + 310.8 + 310.4 + 310.6 + 310.5 + 310.0 + 310.0 + 310.1 + 310.2 = 6513.4 \\)\nAverage in Kelvin: \\( 6513.4 / 21 = 310.1619 \\) (rounded to four decimal places)\n\n**Rankine:**\n\\( 558.7 + 558.6 + 558.1 + 557.7 + 558.1 + 558.3 + 558.3 + 558.7 + 558.6 + 558.0 + 558.7 + 559.1 + 558.3 + 559.4 + 558.7 + 559.1 + 558.9 + 558.1 + 558.1 + 558.2 + 558.3 = 11723.3 \\)\nAverage in Rankine: \\( 11723.3 / 21 = 558.2524 \\) (rounded to four decimal places)\n\nBerry's average temperature during the week is approximately:\n- 37.1143°C\n- 310.1619 K\n- 558.2524°R",
