    "id": 9142,
    "question": "Determine the mass percentage of each element in the following compound: Na2[Cr2(H2O)2(BO3)(OH)4]·8H2O. Additionally, calculate the mass of the compound formed when 50 g of Na2B4O7, 40 g of Cr(NO3)3, and 30 g of NaOH are allowed to react, given the balanced equation:\n\n4 Na2B4O7 + 2 Cr(NO3)3 + 16 NaOH → 4 Na2[Cr2(H2O)2(BO3)(OH)4]·8H2O + 12 NaNO3.\n\n### Answer:",
    "options": [
      "Option A",
      "Option B",
      "Option C",
      "Option D"
    ],
    "correct": 0,
    "explanation": "First, let's determine the molar mass of the compound Na2[Cr2(H2O)2(BO3)(OH)4]·8H2O.\n\nThe molar masses of the elements are approximately:\n- Na: 22.99 g/mol\n- Cr: 51.996 g/mol\n- H: 1.008 g/mol\n- O: 15.999 g/mol\n- B: 10.81 g/mol\n\nThe compound has:\n- 2 Na atoms\n- 2 Cr atoms\n- 2 + 4 + 8(2) = 2 + 4 + 16 = 22 H atoms\n- 2 + 3 + 4(1) + 8(1) = 2 + 3 + 4 + 8 = 17 O atoms from the complex and 8 more from the waters of hydration, totaling 25 O atoms\n- 1 B atom\n\nCalculating the molar mass:\n- Na: 2(22.99) = 45.98 g/mol\n- Cr: 2(51.996) = 103.992 g/mol\n- H: 22(1.008) = 22.176 g/mol\n- O: 25(15.999) = 399.975 g/mol\n- B: 1(10.81) = 10.81 g/mol\n\nTotal molar mass = 45.98 + 103.992 + 22.176 + 399.975 + 10.81 = 582.933 g/mol\n\nNow, let's calculate the mass percentage of each element:\n- Na: (45.98 / 582.933) * 100% = 7.89%\n- Cr: (103.992 / 582.933) * 100% = 17.84%\n- H: (22.176 / 582.933) * 100% = 3.80%\n- O: (399.975 / 582.933) * 100% = 68.61%\n- B: (10.81 / 582.933) * 100% = 1.85%\n\nNext, let's calculate the mass of the compound formed from the given reactants. We need to find the limiting reagent first.\n\nThe molar masses of the reactants are approximately:\n- Na2B4O7: 201.22 g/mol\n- Cr(NO3)3: 238.011 g/mol\n- NaOH: 39.997 g/mol\n\nThe moles of each reactant are:\n- Na2B4O7: 50 g / 201.22 g/mol = 0.2484 mol\n- Cr(NO3)3: 40 g / 238.011 g/mol = 0.1681 mol\n- NaOH: 30 g / 39.997 g/mol = 0.7502 mol\n\nFrom the balanced equation, we see that the stoichiometry is:\n- 4 moles of Na2B4O7 react with 2 moles of Cr(NO3)3 and 16 moles of NaOH.\n\nSo, the limiting reagent is Cr(NO3)3 because it will run out first:\n- 0.1681 mol Cr(NO3)3 * (4 mol Na2[Cr2(H2O)2(BO3)(OH)4]·8H2O / 2 mol Cr(NO3)3) = 0.3362 mol of Na2[Cr2(H2O)2(BO3)(OH)4]·8H2O\n\nNow, we can calculate the mass of the compound formed:\n- 0.3362 mol * 582.933 g/mol = 196.01 g\n\nTherefore, the mass of the compound formed when 50 g of Na2B4O7, 40 g of Cr(NO3)3, and 30 g of NaOH are allowed to react is approximately 196.01 g.",
