    "question": "In Country Z, there are three main employment sectors: A, B, and C. Additionally, there are four different educational qualifications: high school diploma, vocational certificate, university diploma, and postgraduate degree.\n\nIn sector A:\n- 60% of the population holds a high school diploma, 10% a vocational certificate, 25% a university diploma, and 5% a postgraduate degree.\n- 10% without a university diploma have the job of their choice.\n- 30% of the people who do not have the job of their choice hold a university diploma or higher.\n- The percentage of people having the job of their choice varies by age group as follows: 30% for age 18-29, 45% for age 30-49, and 25% for age 50 and above.\n\nIn sector B:\n- 50% of the population has a high school diploma, 20% a vocational certificate, 25% a university diploma, and 5% a postgraduate degree.\n- 5% without a university diploma have the job of their choice.\n- 35% of the people who do not have the job of their choice hold a university diploma or higher.\n- The percentage of people having the job of their choice varies by age group as follows: 20% for age 18-29, 50% for age 30-49, and 30% for age 50 and above.\n\nIn sector C:\n- 40% of the population holds a high school diploma, 20% a vocational certificate, 30% a university diploma, and 10% a postgraduate degree.\n- 15% without a university diploma have the job of their choice.\n- 25% of the people who do not have the job of their choice hold a university diploma or higher.\n- The percentage of people having the job of their choice varies by age group as follows: 25% for age 18-29, 35% for age 30-49, and 40% for age 50 and above.\n\nOverall, 40% of the people in Country Z have the job of their choice. In addition, 30% of the total population works in sector A, 40% works in sector B, and 30% works in sector C. Age distribution is as follows: 40% are between 18-29 years old, 45% are between 30-49 years old, and 15% are 50 years old and above.\n\nCalculate the overall percentage of people in Country Z, across all employment sectors and age groups, who hold a university diploma or higher educational qualification.\n\n### Answer:",
