    "id": 9145,
    "question": "Haley has 63 magazines in her cabinet with varying weights. She plans to send them to the recycling office in their area. Each box can contain up to 9 magazines and has a weight limit of 15 pounds. The weights (in pounds) of the magazines are as follows:\n\n1. 1.6, 1.4, 1.3, 1.8, 2.2, 1.5, 2.1, 1.9, 1.7\n2. 2.3, 1.5, 1.1, 1.6, 1.9, 2.2, 2.0, 1.3, 2.4\n3. 1.8, 1.3, 1.5, 1.7, 1.9, 1.4, 2.1, 2.3, 1.6\n4. 1.4, 1.7, 2.4, 2.0, 1.5, 1.6, 1.1, 1.8, 1.9\n5. 2.2, 1.6, 2.0, 1.3, 1.9, 1.1, 1.7, 2.3, 1.5\n6. 1.5, 1.5, 1.3, 1.7, 1.6, 2.4, 2.1, 1.9, 1.8\n7. 2.1, 2.0, 1.5, 1.1, 1.6, 1.8, 1.3, 1.6, 1.9\n\nIf Haley needs to optimize her box packing to use the least number of boxes without exceeding the weight limit, how should she pack the magazines into the boxes? \n\n### Answer:",
