    "id": 9147,
    "question": "Manex is a seasoned tour bus driver who has a particularly long and varied trip ahead of him. He has to navigate to five different destinations, each with unique road conditions, distances to travel, and duration of stay.\n\nDestination 1: The first stop is 70 miles away on a smooth stretch of road that allows for a speed of 60 mph. Once he arrives, he is scheduled to stay for 1 hour.\n\nDestination 2: The second destination is another 50 miles onward, but due to construction work, the bus is slowed to an average of 35 mph. The layover at this stop is a lengthy 3 hours.\n\nDestination 3: Next, he sets off on a 40-mile journey to the third stop. The first half of this leg is a smooth ride at a constant 60 mph, but the latter half is up a mountainside, reducing the speed to 30 mph. Here, he stays for a 2-hour break.\n\nDestination 4: His fourth road trip is a long 90 miles where the first 30 miles have a speed limit of 40 mph due to it being a wildlife conservation area. The next 60 miles are on a high-speed expressway allowing speeds of up to 70 mph. Upon reaching, he has a 2.5-hour stop.\n\nDestination 5: The final stop is 60 miles away on a scenic but winding coastal road with an average speed limit of 35 mph. His stop here is the briefest, at 45 minutes.\n\nThe return journey covers a different route that is an even 100 miles longer than the outbound journey. This stretch of the trip can be covered at a steady speed of 55 mph. \n\nHow long will the entire journey – including driving and the duration of stays at all destinations – take Manex in hours?\n\n\n### Answer:",
