    "explanation": "Let's calculate the driving time for each leg of the journey first, then add the duration of stays at each destination.\n\n**Destination 1:**\n- Distance: 70 miles\n- Speed: 60 mph\n- Time = Distance / Speed = 70 / 60 = 1.1667 hours\n\n**Destination 2:**\n- Distance: 50 miles\n- Speed: 35 mph\n- Time = Distance / Speed = 50 / 35 = 1.4286 hours\n\n**Destination 3:**\nFor the third destination, we have two different speeds for two different halves of the journey.\n- First half: 20 miles at 60 mph\n- Time = Distance / Speed = 20 / 60 = 0.3333 hours\n- Second half: 20 miles at 30 mph\n- Time = Distance / Speed = 20 / 30 = 0.6667 hours\n- Total time for Destination 3 = 0.3333 + 0.6667 = 1 hour\n\n**Destination 4:**\nAgain, we have two different speeds for two different parts of the journey.\n- First part: 30 miles at 40 mph\n- Time = Distance / Speed = 30 / 40 = 0.75 hours\n- Second part: 60 miles at 70 mph\n- Time = Distance / Speed = 60 / 70 = 0.8571 hours\n- Total time for Destination 4 = 0.75 + 0.8571 = 1.6071 hours\n\n**Destination 5:**\n- Distance: 60 miles\n- Speed: 35 mph\n- Time = Distance / Speed = 60 / 35 = 1.7143 hours\n\n**Return Journey:**\n- Additional Distance: 100 miles\n- Total Return Distance = (70 + 50 + 40 + 90 + 60 + 100) miles\n- Total Return Distance = 410 miles\n- Speed: 55 mph\n- Time = Distance / Speed = 410 / 55 = 7.4545 hours\n\nNow, let's add up all the driving times and the duration of stays at each destination.\n\nTotal driving time = 1.1667 + 1.4286 + 1 + 1.6071 + 1.7143 + 7.4545 hours\nTotal driving time = 14.3712 hours\n\nTotal duration of stays = 1 + 3 + 2 + 2.5 + 0.75 hours\nTotal duration of stays = 9.25 hours\n\nThe entire journey time = Total driving time + Total duration of stays\nThe entire journey time = 14.3712 + 9.25 hours\nThe entire journey time = 23.6212 hours\n\nRounded to the nearest hour, the entire journey will take Manex approximately 24 hours.",
