    "explanation": "Let's start by applying the conditions to the given equations to find the coefficients.\n\n1) f(-1) = g(2)\nUsing f(x) = x^4 - 5x^3 + ax^2 + bx + c, we get:\nf(-1) = (-1)^4 - 5(-1)^3 + a(-1)^2 + b(-1) + c\nf(-1) = 1 + 5 + a - b + c\nf(-1) = a - b + c + 6\n\nUsing g(x) = -2x^5 + 7x^4 - 3x^3 - x^2 + dx + e, we get:\ng(2) = -2(2)^5 + 7(2)^4 - 3(2)^3 - (2)^2 + d(2) + e\ng(2) = -2(32) + 7(16) - 3(8) - 4 + 2d + e\ng(2) = -64 + 112 - 24 - 4 + 2d + e\ng(2) = 2d + e + 20\n\nSetting f(-1) equal to g(2), we get:\na - b + c + 6 = 2d + e + 20\na - b + c - 2d - e = 14  (Equation 1)\n\n2) g(-1) = h(2)\nUsing g(x) again, we get:\ng(-1) = -2(-1)^5 + 7(-1)^4 - 3(-1)^3 - (-1)^2 + d(-1) + e\ng(-1) = 2 + 7 + 3 - 1 - d + e\ng(-1) = e - d + 11\n\nUsing h(x) = x^6 + 2x^5 - 4x^4 + 3x^3 - 2x^2 + fx + g, we get:\nh(2) = (2)^6 + 2(2)^5 - 4(2)^4 + 3(2)^3 - 2(2)^2 + f(2) + g\nh(2) = 64 + 2(32) - 4(16) + 3(8) - 2(4) + 2f + g\nh(2) = 64 + 64 - 64 + 24 - 8 + 2f + g\nh(2) = 2f + g + 80\n\nSetting g(-1) equal to h(2), we get:\ne - d + 11 = 2f + g + 80\ne - d - 2f - g = 69  (Equation 2)\n\n3) h(-2) = f(1)\nUsing h(x) again, we get:\nh(-2) = (-2)^6 + 2(-2)^5 - 4(-2)^4 + 3(-2)^3 - 2(-2)^2 + f(-2) + g\nh(-2) = 64 - 2(32) - 4(16) + 3(-8) - 2(4) - 2f + g\nh(-2) = 64 - 64 - 64 - 24 - 8 - 2f + g\nh(-2) = g - 2f - 96\n\nUsing f(x) again, we get:\nf(1) = (1)^4 - 5(1)^3 + a(1)^2 + b(1) + c\nf(1) = 1 - 5 + a + b + c\nf(1) = a + b + c - 4\n\nSetting h(-2) equal to f(1), we get:\ng - 2f - 96 = a + b + c - 4\na + b + c - g + 2f = 92  (Equation 3)\n\nNow we have three equations with seven unknowns, which means we have an underdetermined system. Without additional information or constraints, we cannot find unique values for the coefficients a, b, c, d, e, f, and g. We would need more conditions to solve for the specific values of these coefficients.",
