    "question": "Cid owns a mechanic shop, and his charges for services vary depending on the car model: \n\n- For Model A cars, he charges $20 for an oil change, $30 for a repair, $5 for a car wash, and $15 for tire rotations.\n- For Model B cars, he charges $25 for an oil change, $40 for a repair, $8 for a car wash, and $18 for tire rotations.\n- For Model C cars, he charges $30 for an oil change, $50 for a repair, $10 for a car wash, and $20 for tire rotations.\n- For Model D cars, he charges $35 for an oil change, $60 for a repair, $12 for a car wash, and $22 for tire rotations.\n\nCid offers a 10% discount on the total bill if a customer gets three or more different services for their car that day.\n\nIn one day, Cid serviced the following cars:\n\n- 5 Model A cars: each had an oil change, a repair, and a car wash\n- 3 Model B cars: each had an oil change, a repair, a car wash, and a tire rotation\n- 2 Model C cars: each had an oil change, a repair, a tire rotation, and a car wash\n- 4 Model D cars: each had an oil change, a repair, and a tire rotation\n\nHow much money did he earn that day, taking into account the discount for multiple services?\n\n### Answer:",
